Terms:
===========================
DBMS  : database management system 
      : collection of data in tabular format (file system)
	-MS Excel
	-MS Access 
	-Foxpro
	etc.	
		
RDBMS : relational database management system
      : collection of data in tabular format with constraints and relationship 
      : and collection of different types of objects
		-function
		-procedure
		-trigger
		-cursor 
		etc.
	: RDBMS works on client -server architecture 
	:There are following tools
		-MS SQL SERVER   *
		-ORACLE
		-MY SQL SERVER	*
		-MONGODB
		-IBMDB2
		etc.



SQL : structual query language (to manage and process the database schema and data)
------------------
Schema: is group of objects (and its structure)


TL-SQL	: transactional structural query language (MS SQL SERVER)
PL-SQL	: procedural structural query language    (ORACLE)


MS SQL SERVER
-----------------------
Client-Server Arichitecture

SSMS : SQL server management studio 
Server : Edtions:

	-Express	: free
	-Professional   : paid
	-Enterprise 	: paid  **
	-Developer edition 


Server Type		: SQL db Engine   *
			MS BI 
			: SSIS  /ETL 
			: SSRS
			: SSAS 
Server/Instance		: IP ADDRESS OR COMPUTER NAME /INSTANCE NAME 
Authentication Type	: 1. WINDOWS 
					There is no id and pwd required 
			  2. SQL 
					id and pwd will be required 

	
