SQL Command Type
======================
DDL	: data definition langauge
	-create		: create new object
	-alter 		: modify structure of object
	-drop 		: remove object
	-truncate 	: vacant table/remove all rows but structure will remain same

DML	: data manipulation langauge
	-insert		: save data 
	-update		: modify value 
	-delete		: remove rows with condition or  without condition 	
DCL	: data control langauge
	-create user
	-grant access
	-revoke access	
TCL	: transaction control language
	-begin transaction 
	-commit 
	-rollback 
DQL	: data query language 
	-select 


**Database: is relational schemal (group of objects) where data can be stored in 

tabular format 
